    "It serves analogous purposes to the blink rate.",
    "• Eye status: Distinguishes between phases when the eye is open and when it is closed.",
    "• Gaze direction: Reflects the eyes' alignment or orientation concerning a specific focal point.",
    "It reveals an observer's current visual attention or point of interest.",
    "• Gaze position: It is the specific point in space or on a surface where a person's eyes are directed or focused."
